*Assessment*

Per documentation for Eucalyptus IAM policy extensions:
{quote}
In IAM, you cannot specify EC2 resources in a policy statement except a wildcard,"*". So, you can't restrict a permission to specific EC2 entities. For example, you can't restrict a user to run instances on a specific image or VM type. To solve that, Eucalyptus created the EC2 resource for the policy language. The following example shows the ARN of an EC2 resource.

{code}arn:aws:ec2::<account_id>:<resource_type>/<resource_id>{code}

Where account id is optional.

Eucalyptus supports the following resource types for EC2:

- image
- securitygroup
- address (either an address or address range: 192.168.7.1-192.168.7.255)
- availabilityzone
- instance
- keypair
- volume
- snapshot
- vmtype
{quote}
The following policy doesn't work in Eucalyptus 4.2 (federated cloud setup):
{code}
[root@h-08 ~]# euare-grouplistpolicies -g limited-ec2 --region devops-admin@asap-rocky-2015 -v
limitied-instance-type
{
  "Version":"2011-04-01",
  "Statement":[{
    "Sid":"2",
    "Effect":"Allow",
    "Action":"ec2:RunInstances",

    "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:ec2:::vmtype/m1.small",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::vmtype/t1.micro",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::image/*",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::securitygroup/*",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::keypair/*",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::availabilityzone/*",
    "arn:aws:ec2:::instance/*"
]

  }]
}

[root@h-08 ~]# euca-run-instances -t t1.micro emi-3992acce --region devops-user02@asap-rocky-2015
euca-run-instances: error (InsufficientInstanceCapacity): Not authorized to create: cpu by user: arn:aws:euare::001476132417:user/user02
[root@h-08 ~]# euca-run-instances -t m1.small emi-3992acce --region devops-user02@asap-rocky-2015
euca-run-instances: error (InsufficientInstanceCapacity): Not authorized to create: cpu by user: arn:aws:euare::001476132417:user/user02
[root@h-08 ~]# euca-run-instances -t m1.medium emi-3992acce --region devops-user02@asap-rocky-2015
euca-run-instances: error (UnauthorizedOperation): Not authorized to allocate vm type m1.medium for arn:aws:euare::001476132417:user/user02
{code}

*Attempted Workarounds*

Tried to add the following ARNs to the IAM policy to see if it would change the outcome:
- {{arn:aws:ec2:::cpu/*}}
- {{arn:aws:ec2:::disk/*}}
- {{arn:aws:ec2:::memory/*}}

However the policy wouldn't load.  The following error would get returned for each ARN:
{code}
[root@h-08 ~]# euare-groupuploadpolicy -p limitied-instance-type -f runinstance-limit-instance-type-v6.policy -g limited-ec2 --region devops-admin@asap-rocky-2015
euare-groupuploadpolicy: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: net.sf.json.JSONException: EC2 type 'cpu' is not supported

[root@h-08 ~]# euare-groupuploadpolicy -p limitied-instance-type -f runinstance-limit-instance-type-v6.policy -g limited-ec2 --region devops-admin@asap-rocky-2015
euare-groupuploadpolicy: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: net.sf.json.JSONException: EC2 type 'disk' is not supported

[root@h-08 ~]# euare-groupuploadpolicy -p limitied-instance-type -f runinstance-limit-instance-type-v6.policy -g limited-ec2 --region devops-admin@asap-rocky-2015
euare-groupuploadpolicy: error (MalformedPolicyDocument): Error in uploaded policy: net.sf.json.JSONException: EC2 type 'memory' is not supported
{code}

